Patients’ agony as hospitals close for 3 weeks over strike             John Oywa  28th Sep 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 John Oywa  28th Sep 2019 00:00:00 GMT +0300 John Oywa   Empty hospital beds at Jaramogi Oginga Odinga Teaching and Referal Hospital in Kisumu on September 11, 2019. Operations at the public hospitals in the county have been paralyzed as medics start their strike over persistent delayed payment. (Collins Oduor, Standard)  Empty hospital beds at Jaramogi Oginga Odinga Teaching and Referal Hospital in Kisumu on September 11, 2019. Operations at the public hospitals in the county have been paralyzed as medics start their strike over persistent delayed payment. (Collins Oduor, Standard) Empty hospital beds at Jaramogi Oginga Odinga Teaching and Referal Hospital in Kisumu on September 11, 2019. Operations at the public hospitals in the county have been paralyzed as medics start their strike over persistent delayed payment. (Collins Oduor, Standard) Empty hospital beds at Jaramogi Oginga Odinga Teaching and Referal Hospital in Kisumu on September 11, 2019. Operations at the public hospitals in the county have been paralyzed as medics start their strike over persistent delayed payment. (Collins Oduor, Standard)       Failure to implement   For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper. For More of This and Other Stories, Grab Your Copy of the Standard Newspaper.         Saturday Standard   “Hakuna kitu hapa ndugu yangu. Wamefunga”        Budget signed     joywa@standardmedia.co.ke joywa@standardmedia.co.ke  We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. We are undertaking a survey to help us improve our content for you. This will only take 1 minute of your time, please give us your feedback by clicking HERE. All responses will be confidential. HERE Related Topics Hopital Closed Nurses S